Charlottesville's police chief said on Monday that it's important not to rush the case against Matthew, despite coming under fire for some of his decisions.

Chief Timothy Longo said on Monday that new information meant investigators believe Graham is in Virginia which has stopped them widening their search beyond state lines.  

Asked whether he expects to find Miss Graham alive, Chief Longo said: 'Every day that passes is not a good sign. Every day that passes translates more to recovery than rescue. But at the end of the day, we still have to find Hannah Graham.'

He added that he thinks about the case constantly.

'I lay in bed at night going over what have we done differently, what could we do differently?' he said.

